Margina (Hungarian: Marzsina; German: Marschina) is a commune in Timiș County, Romania. It is composed of nine villages: Breazova (Hungarian: Béganyiresd; German: Brassova), Bulza (Hungarian: Bulza), Coșevița (Hungarian: Kiskossó), Coșteiu de Sus (Hungarian: Felsőkastély), Groși (Hungarian: Marosgórós; German: Gross), Margina, Nemeșești (Hungarian: Nemcse; German: Nemesest), Sintești (Hungarian: Bégaszentes) and Zorani (Hungarian: Zorány).